---
import Tag from "../components/ui/Tag.astro";
export const partial = true;

const pageTitle = "idkz - projects";
---

<title>{pageTitle}</title>
<div class="w-full flex flex-wrap gap-8 justify-center">
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-12 border p-4 w-full rounded-md shadow-lg bg-largecard">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-between w-full ">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tighter">BBY SKU Setup Portal</h1>
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <a href="https://bby-htmx.vercel.app/" target="_blank">
          <button
            class="p-2 border rounded-md bg-btn text-btntext font-medium hover:opacity-80"
            >View Project</button
          ></a
        >

        <a href="https://github.com/i-dkz/bby-htmx" target="_blank">
          <button
            class="p-2 border rounded-md bg-btn text-btntext font-medium hover:opacity-80"
            >View Git Repo</button
          ></a
        >
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex gap-8 flex-wrap sm:flex-nowrap">
      <div class="w-[350px] lg:w-[50%]">
        <img src="/bby-htmx.png" alt="" class="rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      </div>
      <div
        class="flex flex-col gap-6 w-[350px] sm:w-[250px] md:w-[300px] lg:w-[50%]"
      >
        <p class="">
          This is a proof of concept to help replace BestBuy's SKU onboarding
          experience for vendors.
        </p>
        <p>
          Users can create an account, login. Once logged in they can begin
          onboarding SKUs. Using javascript they can upload excel files, and the
          app has the ability to read text pdf's and sends an API request to
          OpenAI to analyze the pdf information. User can select from the
          uploaded pdf and the corresponding MSDS information autopopulates the
          form.
        </p>
        <div class="w-full flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
          <Tag title="Astro" />
          <Tag title="HTMX" />
          <Tag title="Alpine.js" />
          <Tag title="JavaScript" />
          <Tag title="Tailwind" />
          <Tag title="ChatGPT" />
          <Tag title="Supabase" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-12 border p-4 w-full rounded-md shadow-lg bg-largecard">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-between w-full">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tighter">nxtStore</h1>
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <a href="https://nxt-store.vercel.app/" target="_blank">
          <button
            class="p-2 border rounded-md bg-btn text-btntext font-medium hover:opacity-80"
            >View Project</button
          ></a
        >

        <a href="https://github.com/i-dkz/nxtStore" target="_blank">
          <button
            class="p-2 border rounded-md bg-btn text-btntext font-medium hover:opacity-80"
            >View Git Repo</button
          ></a
        >
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex gap-8 flex-wrap sm:flex-nowrap">
      <div class="w-[350px] lg:w-[50%]">
        <img src="/nxtstore.png" alt="" class="rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      </div>
      <div
        class="flex flex-col gap-6 w-[350px] sm:w-[250px] md:w-[300px] lg:w-[50%]"
      >
        <p class="">
          The aim of this project was to demonstrate my ability to create a
          nice, modern storefront, capable of requesting data from an API and
          displaying the data to the user.
        </p>
        <p>
          The user can add and delete items from the cart, and search for items.
        </p>
        <div class="w-full flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
          <Tag title="Next.js" />
          <Tag title="React.js" />
          <Tag title="Zustand" />
          <Tag title="Tailwind" />
          <Tag title="Axios" />
          <Tag title="Shadcn" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-12 border p-4 w-full rounded-md shadow-lg mb-12 bg-largecard">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-between w-full">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tighter">Gameplus</h1>
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <a href="https://grand-monstera-b8f151.netlify.app/" target="_blank">
          <button
            class="p-2 border rounded-md bg-btn text-btntext font-medium hover:opacity-80"
            >View Project
          </button></a
        >
  
        <a href="https://github.com/i-dkz/react-refresh" target="_blank">
          <button
            class="p-2 border rounded-md bg-btn text-btntext font-medium hover:opacity-80"
            >View Git Repo</button
          ></a
        >
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex gap-8 flex-wrap sm:flex-nowrap">
      <div class="w-[350px] lg:w-[50%]">
        <img src="/gameplus1.jpeg" alt="" class="rounded-md shadow-lg" />
      </div>
      <div
        class="flex flex-col gap-6 w-[350px] sm:w-[250px] md:w-[300px] lg:w-[50%]"
      >
        <p class="">
          This is a game directory app that shows up to date games from the
          RAWG.io API. The user has search functionality, and filtering to find
          the most up to date games.
        </p>
  
        <div class="w-full flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
          <Tag title="React.js" />
          <Tag title="ChakraUI" />
          <Tag title="Axios" />
          <Tag title="Vite" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

